WHO   — The 128-Dimensional Head — the per-head subspace · 64 then 128
WHAT  — The honest number: Vaswani's base model used d_k=64 (512/8); large modern models (Llama 2 70B, GPT-3 175B) use 128 — a bigger room for each head to work in.
WHERE — TTU1 · Transformer Tech Universe  Framework inputs: Attention Is All You Need (Vaswani 2017); interpretability literature; David's deck encoding  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because 'how big is a head' is a real design knob, and the answer moved — the original 64 is not a law, and 128 is now common at scale.
HOW   — By d_k = d_model / h: choose the model width and the head count, and the head dimension falls out (often 64 or 128).

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the room each head thinks in — 64 wide when the field began, 128 wide at modern scale; not a constant, a choice.

